      • setInt

        public void setInt​(java.lang.String name,
                   int value)
        Convenience setter for tasks that keep lots of numeric statistics. Convert to the int to a String but only store it if it is non-zero to avoid cluttering up the result. If it is zero and a value for it exists, remove the value.

      • addInt

        public void addInt​(java.lang.String name,
                   int value)
        Add to the possible previous value of an attribute. This must be used by tasks that maintain worker threads with their own statistics that are merged at the end.
